{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Added the initial architecture docs for prompt 09. The core additions are [0001-core-runtime-architecture.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md) and [system-diagram.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_53", "text": "Added the initial architecture docs for prompt 09. The core additions are [0001-core-runtime-architecture.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md) and [system-diagram.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/system-diagram.md), with supporting link updates in [architecture-overview.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/architecture-overview.md), [docs/README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/README.md), [docs/adr/README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/adr/README.md), and [README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/README.md). The ADR now fixes the main architectural decisions: backend-owned Gemini access, Postgres as the durable source of truth, file-backed GCS storage for artifacts, WebSocket live updates, separate workers for long-running jobs, and soft planning constraints for word count, runtime, and chapters.\n\nVerification passed with `make check` and a docs-specific Prettier check. That covered backend pytest `11/11`, frontend Vitest `2/2`, frontend lint/build, backend lint/format checks, and Markdown formatting for `README.md` plus all files under `docs/`. No browser or screenshot verification was needed because this task only changed documentation. I checkpointed the docs work in commit `c9bf1d5` (`feat(prompt-09): initial system diagram and adr`), and the required final reviewer summary is at [09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.summary.md).", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 98, "prompt_index": 10, "prompt_name": "09 \u2014 Initial System Diagram and First Architecture Decisions", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-03-31T22:19:19-07:00"}
